A 96-year-old woman is missing from a town in south Wales. Rita, has not been seen since leaving her home in the Brecon Beacons at around 10.20am on Saturday, Dyfed-Powys Police said. The elderly woman, whose surname has not been revealed, is thought to be on foot and wearing a fleece with a leaf design. A picture has been released of her with short white hair and glasses. She is from Brecon – a picturesque town which attracts huge numbers of hikers and tourists in the summer. Officers say they are concerned for her welfare and appealing for anyone who may have information on her whereabouts to contact them. Those who think they can help are asked to call police on 101, or email 101@dyfed-powys.police.uk, quoting reference DP-20220226-221. Metro.co.uk has contacted the force for more information. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page. MORE : Family Reunion’s Jaida Benjamin found safe after missing person report sparked celebrity appeals